== Iterative procedures ==
Except for special cases, the likelihood equations
formula_171

cannot be solved explicitly for an estimator formula_172. Instead, they need to be solved iteratively: starting from an initial guess of formula_16 (say formula_174), one seeks to obtain a convergent sequence formula_175. Many methods for this kind of optimization problem are available, but the most commonly used ones are algorithms based on an updating formula of the form
formula_176

where the vector formula_177 indicates the descent direction of the rth &quot;step,&quot; and the scalar formula_178 captures the &quot;step length,&quot; also known as the learning rate.

=== Gradient descent method ===
